<font color="#FF0000">DOING SOMETHING ABOUT IT...</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 18 20:42:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
In response as to what we can do now...I once heard John Fogerty at a welcome home concert say to write it in a letter to him and then just dropit and get on with life.  I thought &quot;what balls&quot; to tell that to a bunch of vets...By the way he is one of my favorites, as I am sure that a bunch of us liked his songs..Anyway I saw the mini wall in 1988 and couldn't stand it..I too like many of my brothers had 5 relationships, countless jobs, traveled around the country trying to escape the horror's of war...Drinking and drugging were the norm.  Well after 5 relationships, 4 children, and I can't even count the drunk driving tickets over the years (I had two licenses, two s. s. numbers, and basically hid out from the rest of society).  I decided to find out what was aling me and making me act this way (oh, I never mentioned the attempted susicide's) (yes, several)(I feel pretty silly about them, I mean you would think that a Govt. trained and certified killer could surely do himself in.)I talked to a consoler in S.C. and found out that I could use the V.A. hosp, because that I was a Viet. Vet.  Well sir I went there , admited myself, went through 60 days on a mental ward and then 30 days in a drug and alcohol rehab ward..I talked to the consolers and physicitrist and anybody that I thought could help...And thank God, I found some help. That was in April of 1993.  (Oh, by the way I am considered 100% disabled because of agent orange, and recieved a nice settlement of $340.00. How special.) Anyway I attend AA on a regular basis (usually 3x's per week)I attend a Unity church for my spiritually, (which I felt was stripped in Nam)and have been to quite a few men's conferences to futher my conscious contact with the God of my choice...I am currently a Project Manager for a construction co.  Two years ago I became a trained Hypnotherapist...I have learned the power of the human mind and prayer..Also I have learned that your world is what you percieve it to be...I had to take my Nam experience and find the good in it and leave the rest...I have been to the wall in D.C. and this time although I did break down, I was able to make peace with it...I now try to help fellow Vets. and Alcoholics..I just recently attended the Promise Keepers at the Pontiac Silverdome...Quite a moving experience...I am going to Manassas this weekend to enjoy veterans day at my daughter and son-in-laws, and the Vet's ceremonys in D.C.  In Oct. the Promise keepers will have a day of prayer for our government. No violence or any of that stuff, just pray for our leaders...I truly see a new outlook in our society and can't help but feel that we as Viet Vets had a lot to do with awakening path that this country is headed on...The Promise Keepers gig is Oct. 4.  That's a Sat and it is from 12 noon until 6PM..It is called Stand in the Gap. For futher info they have a web site at www.promisekeepers.org. or 1-800-417-1878..At the Silver dome we were 55,000 strong and did a satilite hook up with L.A. which had us over 100,000 strong at one time...It was truly powerful.  I used to think that I could as one person not make any difference.  I never even used the right to vote until a couple years ago...I always felt that we were voting for the lesser of two evils...I now realize that if we do not express our opinions and wants, that other people will express thiers and we will be rulled by what they want and not by what we want...We just can't sit back any longer...It's time we do like the ole D.I. used to say when he said &quot;Bend over and reach around with both hands, grab yourself by both ears, and pull...And when I hear that loud pop, I'll know that you have your head out of your rectum.&quot;  We have a need to excert our experience's and wisdom on this Great Nation of ours...If it takes change then so be it...It ain't gonna happen if we sit on our duff's...We don't want another Nam???How we gonna stop it???We need to take our country back...I see the Promise Keepers as a good thing, worth pursuing, and a great thing for us to teach our children and grandchildren...In the bible it states that if we teach our children the road to rightiousness that they will not stray far, and always return to the right road...The trouble is that we have to teach them...Make a conscious effort...I can assure you that as a Vietnam Vet, that I will continue to make that a priority in my life...I am compelled and driven to make this earth a better place for having me in it...A better place for all...&quot;When we are born we cry and the world celebrates, but live your life so that when you die the world cries and you celebrate.&quot;  Unknown...I will be doing my part.  Will you???
